## Branch naming rule

- Language: English only, clear and concise.
- Format: `<type>/<short-kebab-description>`
  - `type`: `feat`, `fix`, `chore`, `docs`, `refactor`, `test`, `style`
  - `short-kebab-description`: kebab-case, no spaces, no uppercase, no accents
- Optional ticket id suffix: `<type>/<short-kebab-description>-<ticketId>`
- Examples (valid):
  - `feat/add-google-login`
  - `fix/user-profile-loading`
  - `refactor/auth-module-structure`
  - `feat/implement-nestjs-gateway-MC-123`
- Examples (invalid):
  - `feat/them-dang-nhap-google` (Vietnamese)
  - `Feat/Add_Google_Login` (uppercase and underscores)
  - `update-login` (missing `type`)

### Workflow reminders

1. Create from `main`: `git pull origin main --rebase && git checkout -b <branch-name>`
2. Keep commits scoped to the branch purpose.
3. Rebase with `main` before PR: `git pull origin main --rebase`.
4. Use Conventional Commits (VN) for commit messages.

